Arch Convoker of Morell Thule<br>
Fury's Edge</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rabidsheep>rabidsheep</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 138<br> <font color=#333333>(12/20/02 8:57:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=481.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: QS3 worth it?</span><hr size=1> And if you have a summoning haste item, thats one second faster then the summoned ring (on pets). Then you get max haste with QS2. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=227830">Rabids Arch Mage</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rabidsheep>rabidsheep</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 139<br> <font color=#333333>(12/20/02 8:58:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=481.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: QS3 worth it?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>SPELL CASTING DEFTNESS DOES NOT EFFECT SUMMONS OR HEALS* do NOT get this worthless ability<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I think the only spell this effects are buffs, like DS, shielding line, burnout and all those.<br>
<br>
Not the best skill we have, no<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=227830">Rabids Arch Mage</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balanzsonofanz>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 2487<br> <font color=#333333>(12/20/02 4:44:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=481.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: QS3 worth it?</span><hr size=1> Five second pets do indeed rule.  If you are reclaiming pets for mana, QS3 shaves a second off your reclaim cycle, so instead of 130 mana, so it is about a 20% increase in your mana generation rate.<br>
<br>
Also, when you ding 61, you are unlikely to have either the 61 summon spell haste ring or an item with spell haste 4.  QS3, on the other hand, will effect your 61+ pets, which take a base 12 seconds to cast.<br>
<br>
However, there is also a new cleric buff that adds spell haste, and appears to stack with both QS3 and item spell haste.<br>
<br>
I am holding back on QS3 until I have <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Host of Elements</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Fury of Magic</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> done, but I bought it before the transvergence refund and was very happy with it then.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Razamatazz Pizzazz</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>EDIT:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Here is an earlier discussion on QS3:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showMessage?topicID=415.topic">Buy back QS?</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balanzsonofanz>Balanz son of Anz</A> at: 12/20/02 4:46:13 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xurtsdunnit>Xurts Dunnit</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 55<br> <font color=#333333>(1/2/03 9:18:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=481.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: QS3 worth it?</span><hr size=1> So, the max spell haste (or at least the max spell haste for summoning pets) is 50%?  You can't get lower than 50% cast times regardless of the AA/focus-haste/Cleric-spell-haste combinations?<br>
<br>
If the answer to that is yes... I will not ever need QS3, IMO.  I get 50% cast times already with QS2, focus haste, and cleric spell haste... and it isn't worth it to me to have to spend 9 pts for the few times I don't have the cleric spell haste buff.  Maybe.. MAYBE.. right before train in MGB. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xoniker>Xoniker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#333333>(2/2/03 11:11:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=481.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   QS3</span><hr size=1> I put this off after the mod rod nerf.  Finally just now trained it now that i'm running out of useful aa at 140 points.<br>
<br>
I LOVE QS3 for pet canni.  <br>
<br>
With QS2 i used to switch out a summoning haste 3 item every time i wanted to pet canni, which was really more annoying clicking than i realized.  With QS3, i now pet canni about 2x as much in between pulls etc, because it's so much less painful. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
You do hit the spell haste cap (50%) with QS2, spiked ring, and Blessing of Reverence.  I don't know why, but I have the hardest time getting clerics to cast that buff though.  Maybe 1 in 20 clerics i run into will keep casters buffed with it.  Usually, if they cast it at all, they will buff the group when it first gets together and then never refresh it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ylaine76>Ylaine76</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1220<br> <font color=#333333>(2/2/03 4:28:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=481.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: QS3</span><hr size=1> Swapping out an item maybe annoying but I find getting 9 AA points even more of a hassle <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I'm sticking with QS2 + summoning haste item for pet canni <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.strike9.com/file.aspx/path=/YlaineEQ/fullsize/cheersig2.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
Ylaine D'esibour<br>
65 Arch Convoker<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=60178">www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=60178</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mavermage>Mavermage</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 385<br> <font color=#333333>(2/3/03 2:42:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=481.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.strike9.com/eq/file.aspx/path=/Maverness/fullsize/NewMaver.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: QS3</span><hr size=1>  I guess getting QS3 depends on whether or not the mage likes to cannapet, and what their equipment is. I have QS1  and VT pants that give an additional 30% haste, so I'll probably only work on getting QS3 once I get the elemental pants. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tuis>Tuis</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 124<br> <font color=#333333>(2/3/03 8:45:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=481.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.elp.rr.com/scythek/everquest/Tuis.JPG height=120 width=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: QS3</span><hr size=1> I'm a big fan of innate abilities and choosing my gear to compliment my potential.  If I can free a slot for a good item by spending a few AA, I'll do it.  For PvP, I like to get a pet out and buffed as fast as possible.  Chopping the cast time in half without item swapping can make the difference.  Freeing up a buff slot so that I won't need cleric spell haste is worth the AA points to me.<br>
<br>
Everyone has their own preferences.  Ask yourself if its worth it to *you* to innately be able to cut your summoning times in half, should items and buffs not be available. <p><a href="http://home.elp.rr.com/scythek/everquest/">Tuis Kagato</a> - Arch Convoker of Karana (<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=175764">Profile</a>) - <a href="http://www.pandemonium.cc/">Deloth's Dudes</a><br>
Beefcake Zergbane - Arch Pet of Tuis<br>

<a href="http://home.elp.rr.com/scythek/everquest/">Wikkn Stormseeker</a> - Druid Assassin of Karana (<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=282772">Profile</a>) - LFG<br>

<br>

Capital punishment for me, capital punishment for all. - <i>Wumpscut</i><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jayteebushwacker>Jaytee Bushwacker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Summoner Da'FoH</span><br>  Posts: 1509<br> <font color=#333333>(2/3/03 12:51:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=481.topic&index=12>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: QS3</span><hr size=1> After QS 2 you hit the point of diminishing returns IMO.  QS2 is 25% iirc.  Add in the 10% from your bracer and your at 35%.  Not quite 50% but on all but CoH and pet summoning spells you are going to be talking a difference of .1 to .2 seconds.  Hardly worth 9 points.<br>
<br>
Also consider when CoH really needs to be as fast as possible just get the cleric 10% spell haste buff. which gets you down to about 7 second CoH. <p><hr>
